#, no-wrap
msgid "v"
msgstr ""

#. type: kindex
#: rmail.texi.orig:1210
#, no-wrap
msgid "v @r{(Rmail)}"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: rmail.texi.orig:1213
msgid "Toggle between @acronym{MIME} display and raw message (@code{rmail-mime})."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: rmail.texi.orig:1224
msgid ""
"Each plain-text @acronym{MIME} part is initially displayed immediately after "
"its tagline, as part of the Rmail buffer, while @acronym{MIME} parts of "
"other types are represented only by their taglines, with their actual "
"contents hidden.  In either case, you can toggle a @acronym{MIME} part "
"between its ``displayed'' and ``hidden'' states by typing @key{RET} anywhere "
"in the part---or anywhere in its tagline (except for buttons for other "
"actions, if there are any).  Type @key{RET} (or click with the mouse) to "
"activate a tagline button, and @key{TAB} to cycle point between tagline "
"buttons."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: rmail.texi.orig:1229
msgid ""
"The @kbd{v} (@code{rmail-mime}) command toggles between the default "
"@acronym{MIME} display described above, and a ``raw'' display showing the "
"undecoded @acronym{MIME} data.  With a prefix argument, this command toggles "
"the display of only an entity at point."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: rmail.texi.orig:1234
msgid ""
"To prevent Rmail from handling MIME decoded messages, change the variable "
"@code{rmail-enable-mime} to @code{nil}.  When this is the case, the @kbd{v} "
"(@code{rmail-mime}) command instead creates a temporary buffer to display "
"the current @acronym{MIME} message."
msgstr ""

